1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:01,876
[Marcus] <i>You disobeyed my order!</i>

2
00:00:01,960 --> 00:00:03,920
<i>You shot and killed so many civilians!</i>

3
00:00:04,004 --> 00:00:07,340
If we hadn't fired first,
we'd be dead by now!

4
00:00:07,424 --> 00:00:09,300
[Marcus] <i>Someone hijacked our comms.</i>

5
00:00:09,384 --> 00:00:11,511
<i>Then someone opened fire,</i>
<i>and chaos broke out.</i>

6
00:00:12,137 --> 00:00:13,555
The mission was a success.

7
00:00:13,638 --> 00:00:15,640
Many innocent people died!

8
00:00:15,724 --> 00:00:17,559
[Marcus] <i>Harold got left behind,</i>
<i>and he's dead!</i>

9
00:00:17,642 --> 00:00:20,103
- Don't you care?!
- [Azuelo] Agent Reyes!

10
00:00:20,186 --> 00:00:23,648
That's why your mission was a success.

11
00:00:23,732 --> 00:00:27,318
[Azuelo] <i>Do your duty for Harold.</i>
<i>Live for him.</i>

12
00:00:27,402 --> 00:00:29,487
Just like you're doing for your brother.

13
00:00:29,571 --> 00:00:32,115
Something went wrong during our mission.

14
00:00:32,198 --> 00:00:36,411
[Marcus] I won't find peace
until I find out what really happened.

15
00:00:36,494 --> 00:00:39,330
[Jamilah] <i>Mama, please take care</i>
<i>of my brother for me.</i>

16
00:00:39,414 --> 00:00:41,124
<i>I will go after Amah.</i>

17
00:00:41,207 --> 00:00:43,877
<i>I can't just sit here and do nothing.</i>

18
00:00:43,960 --> 00:00:45,754
<i>I have to save him.</i>

19
00:00:45,837 --> 00:00:49,007
[Azuelo] <i>We,</i>
<i>along with the entire police force,</i>

20
00:00:49,090 --> 00:00:53,011
<i>vow to end the proliferation</i>
<i>of illegal weapons,</i>

21
00:00:53,094 --> 00:00:55,722
<i>not only in Datu Rahman's community,</i>

22
00:00:55,805 --> 00:00:57,432
<i>but across the country.</i>

23
00:01:01,519 --> 00:01:07,442
[mysterious theme music playing]

24
00:01:25,251 --> 00:01:31,841
[gloomy music playing]

25
00:01:44,521 --> 00:01:47,732
[critters chirping]

26
00:01:48,817 --> 00:01:55,198
[breathing heavily]

27
00:01:56,533 --> 00:02:00,620
[Azuelo] Agent Reyes, the man of the hour.

28
00:02:00,703 --> 00:02:02,622
Congratulations.

29
00:02:05,083 --> 00:02:05,959
[rebel in Tausug] <i>For God!</i>

30
00:02:06,543 --> 00:02:08,628
[gunshots blasting]

31
00:02:08,711 --> 00:02:10,130
[rebel in Tausug] For God!

32
00:02:10,213 --> 00:02:11,548
- [blade clinks]
- [grunts]

33
00:02:11,631 --> 00:02:13,216
- [gunshots blasting]
- [groaning]

34
00:02:13,299 --> 00:02:14,134
[gunshots blasting]

35
00:02:14,217 --> 00:02:16,970
- [gunshots blasting]
- [screams]

36
00:02:17,053 --> 00:02:23,017
[grim music playing]

37
00:02:23,101 --> 00:02:25,353
[grunting]

38
00:02:30,984 --> 00:02:33,945
- [rapid gunfire]
- [grunts]

39
00:02:36,614 --> 00:02:38,575
[Felix grunting]

40
00:02:38,658 --> 00:02:40,243
Why are there only four of you?

41
00:02:40,827 --> 00:02:41,995
Where's Harold?

42
00:02:43,204 --> 00:02:45,623
[Felix] Sir, we have to move now.

43
00:02:45,707 --> 00:02:47,083
We're in a dangerous position here.

44
00:02:47,167 --> 00:02:48,209
- [distant gunshots]
- [shouting]

45
00:02:48,293 --> 00:02:49,919
- [shouts]
- [grunts]

46
00:02:50,003 --> 00:02:52,422
[rapid gunfire]

47
00:02:52,505 --> 00:02:54,757
[Marcus] Come on, come on! Let's move!

48
00:02:55,383 --> 00:02:57,594
[Felix] <i>Sir! This is war!</i>

49
00:02:57,677 --> 00:03:00,179
<i>They're going to kill us!</i>

50
00:03:00,263 --> 00:03:03,141
[gunshots]

51
00:03:04,767 --> 00:03:07,437
- [gunshots]
- [screams]

52
00:03:07,520 --> 00:03:09,772
[rapid beeping]

53
00:03:09,856 --> 00:03:12,442
[suspenseful music playing]

54
00:03:18,281 --> 00:03:19,157
[rapid beeping]

55
00:03:19,240 --> 00:03:22,118
- [gunshots]
- [screams]

56
00:03:23,453 --> 00:03:27,248
[clacking, whirring]

57
00:03:33,212 --> 00:03:35,590
[suspenseful music continues]

58
00:03:37,175 --> 00:03:38,301
[whirring beep]

59
00:03:54,442 --> 00:03:55,568
[Jean sniffles]

60
00:03:57,570 --> 00:03:59,030
Here's the photo of you and Erick.

61
00:03:59,697 --> 00:04:03,743
[pensive music playing]

62
00:04:05,119 --> 00:04:07,914
[breath quivers]

63
00:04:07,997 --> 00:04:10,583
[Marcus] Oliver brought that with him
on every mission.

64
00:04:12,752 --> 00:04:15,546
He held on to it
until he lost consciousness.

65
00:04:16,881 --> 00:04:19,300
[crying]

66
00:04:22,387 --> 00:04:24,389
[breath quivers]

67
00:04:28,810 --> 00:04:30,144
Thank you, sir.

68
00:04:30,228 --> 00:04:31,980
Jean, please forgive me.

69
00:04:34,857 --> 00:04:37,068
I failed to protect Oliver.

70
00:04:37,777 --> 00:04:39,153
[soft sobbing]

71
00:04:39,237 --> 00:04:41,239
I couldn't control what happened.

72
00:04:41,322 --> 00:04:42,490
[sniffles]

73
00:04:43,491 --> 00:04:46,244
You don't have to blame yourself, sir.

74
00:04:46,327 --> 00:04:53,084
At least you brought him back alive…

75
00:04:54,544 --> 00:04:56,212
to me and my son.

76
00:04:57,297 --> 00:05:01,384
[pensive music continues]

77
00:05:02,051 --> 00:05:05,680
[sobbing softly]

78
00:05:12,562 --> 00:05:14,105
- Ma'am?
- Oh.

79
00:05:14,188 --> 00:05:16,733
Sir Oliver's test results
have been released.

80
00:05:16,816 --> 00:05:18,735
- And it's all cleared.
- Okay.

81
00:05:18,818 --> 00:05:21,988
As you can see,
he is still unconscious but stable.

82
00:05:22,989 --> 00:05:25,283
- [Jean] Thank God.
- [nurse] Excuse me.

83
00:05:25,366 --> 00:05:26,409
Uh, Nurse?

84
00:05:26,492 --> 00:05:29,370
How are my two colleagues?
Marquez and Contreras.

85
00:05:29,454 --> 00:05:30,580
Same condition, sir.

86
00:05:30,663 --> 00:05:33,333
Tests and stats are good,
but still unconscious.

87
00:05:34,417 --> 00:05:35,460
Excuse me.

88
00:05:35,543 --> 00:05:39,464
[somber music playing]

89
00:05:39,547 --> 00:05:43,176
[phone vibrating]

90
00:05:44,427 --> 00:05:45,386
Lara.

91
00:05:47,472 --> 00:05:48,514
What?

92
00:05:52,268 --> 00:05:56,147
[foreboding music playing]

93
00:05:58,441 --> 00:05:59,525
[Lara] Marcus.

94
00:06:00,359 --> 00:06:02,028
What do you mean the files were deleted?

95
00:06:02,111 --> 00:06:04,072
Hold on. Someone might hear you.

96
00:06:04,739 --> 00:06:06,115
[door clicks open]

97
00:06:06,199 --> 00:06:07,784
- Lara!
- Hold on!

98
00:06:08,826 --> 00:06:10,119
[door clicks open]

99
00:06:10,203 --> 00:06:12,121
[suspenseful music]

100
00:06:12,205 --> 00:06:13,372
[door clicks shut]

101
00:06:17,126 --> 00:06:18,294
[Lara] Look.

102
00:06:18,377 --> 00:06:20,171
Nothing. All the footage is wiped out.

103
00:06:21,297 --> 00:06:22,423
All of the video files are gone.

104
00:06:23,674 --> 00:06:25,009
- Have you tried this one?
- Yes, ma'am.

105
00:06:25,093 --> 00:06:27,637
All of the files were gone?
Not even one was left?

106
00:06:27,720 --> 00:06:29,931
- [Marcus] Even the SD cards?
- Yes. They're all corrupted.

107
00:06:30,014 --> 00:06:32,266
[digital trilling]

108
00:06:32,350 --> 00:06:34,852
[suspensful music]

109
00:06:34,936 --> 00:06:35,978
[Marcus] Lara.

110
00:06:36,729 --> 00:06:38,731
It's impossible that this
is just a coincidence.

111
00:06:39,816 --> 00:06:41,150
That's what I thought too.

112
00:06:44,195 --> 00:06:45,696
Don't worry.

113
00:06:45,780 --> 00:06:48,116
I'll investigate everyone
who has direct access here.

114
00:06:51,077 --> 00:06:52,453
If all of our comms were hijacked,

115
00:06:54,497 --> 00:06:56,249
maybe it's just one person
who is responsible for this.

116
00:06:57,792 --> 00:06:58,960
How did that person delete all the files?

117
00:06:59,043 --> 00:07:01,796
Who's sabotaging us, and for what reason?

118
00:07:01,879 --> 00:07:07,552
[foreboding music continues]

119
00:07:11,389 --> 00:07:12,432
[music fades]

120
00:07:12,515 --> 00:07:17,728
[pensive music playing]

121
00:07:17,812 --> 00:07:19,939
Who are you working for?

122
00:07:21,274 --> 00:07:24,026
Where do you get the weapons
dropped on your island?

123
00:07:24,110 --> 00:07:26,154
I don't know what you're talking about.

124
00:07:26,821 --> 00:07:29,115
None of your accusations
against me is true.

125
00:07:29,198 --> 00:07:31,826
Datu Rahman, I saw the guns.
They were there.

126
00:07:32,577 --> 00:07:34,036
You even used it to fight us.

127
00:07:35,329 --> 00:07:37,498
You fired guns at our community.

128
00:07:37,582 --> 00:07:39,000
We just defended ourselves.

129
00:07:39,083 --> 00:07:41,210
The weapons you saw,

130
00:07:41,294 --> 00:07:43,421
we got them from the sea.

131
00:07:43,504 --> 00:07:46,632
And we hid it from the syndicate
so they couldn't use it.

132
00:07:50,970 --> 00:07:52,305
Why didn't you surrender the weapons?

133
00:07:54,307 --> 00:07:55,808
Surrender to who?

134
00:07:58,603 --> 00:07:59,896
To people like you?

135
00:07:59,979 --> 00:08:01,856
Don't try to turn this around.

136
00:08:02,773 --> 00:08:04,233
You are the criminal here.

137
00:08:04,317 --> 00:08:05,568
[thud]

138
00:08:08,779 --> 00:08:10,198
You arrested me.

139
00:08:11,908 --> 00:08:13,743
Paraded me like an animal.

140
00:08:15,286 --> 00:08:17,413
But it was you who killed children.

141
00:08:18,122 --> 00:08:19,332
You killed women

142
00:08:20,291 --> 00:08:22,960
and the defenseless elderly.

143
00:08:24,879 --> 00:08:26,339
Now tell me!

144
00:08:28,424 --> 00:08:30,968
Who is the real criminal?

145
00:08:31,594 --> 00:08:37,391
[dramatic music playing]

146
00:08:37,475 --> 00:08:43,814
[gunshots]

147
00:08:47,318 --> 00:08:50,738
[dramatic music continues]

148
00:09:07,421 --> 00:09:09,632
Datu Rahman is really tough, huh?

149
00:09:14,512 --> 00:09:15,596
Marcus.

150
00:09:17,265 --> 00:09:21,102
Don't tell me you're affected
by what that criminal said?

151
00:09:23,396 --> 00:09:25,064
He's a master manipulator.

152
00:09:25,147 --> 00:09:27,692
You saw what his people
from the island will do for him.

153
00:09:28,484 --> 00:09:30,820
They're willing to die for him.

154
00:09:30,903 --> 00:09:32,572
Don't let him get to your head.

155
00:09:33,281 --> 00:09:35,199
He can't control me.

156
00:09:37,243 --> 00:09:38,536
But it seems like…

157
00:09:39,412 --> 00:09:41,247
something's not making sense.

158
00:09:41,831 --> 00:09:42,957
What do you mean?

159
00:09:43,040 --> 00:09:47,587
[morose music playing]

160
00:09:56,637 --> 00:09:58,556
I was just removing a…

161
00:10:03,394 --> 00:10:04,478
It's gone.

162
00:10:10,276 --> 00:10:14,363
[somber music]

163
00:10:18,743 --> 00:10:20,119
[woman crying] Everyone!

164
00:10:20,953 --> 00:10:23,414
[crying] Look, everyone!

165
00:10:23,497 --> 00:10:24,832
Look!

166
00:10:24,915 --> 00:10:27,001
[crying] Look!

167
00:10:27,084 --> 00:10:30,588
My child caught this on video.
Look! Oh my God!

168
00:10:30,671 --> 00:10:32,381
- [woman] What is that?
- Look!

169
00:10:32,465 --> 00:10:33,633
What is that?

170
00:10:34,133 --> 00:10:35,384
[In Arabic] Allah is greater!

171
00:10:35,468 --> 00:10:37,178
[woman crying]

172
00:10:37,261 --> 00:10:42,350
[overlapping clamor]

173
00:10:42,433 --> 00:10:47,772
[grim music playing]

174
00:10:50,232 --> 00:10:54,570
[pensive music playing]

175
00:11:14,298 --> 00:11:18,052
[pensive music continues]

176
00:11:18,135 --> 00:11:20,096
- [radio beeps]
- [man] <i>Neutralize the area.</i>

177
00:11:20,179 --> 00:11:21,639
<i>No civilians there.</i>

178
00:11:21,722 --> 00:11:22,890
- <i>You're walking into an ambush!</i>
- [radio beeps]

179
00:11:25,142 --> 00:11:30,773
[pensive music continues]

180
00:11:47,081 --> 00:11:48,249
[gunshots]

181
00:11:55,381 --> 00:11:58,843
[pensive music continues]

182
00:12:23,617 --> 00:12:24,743
[distant gunfire]

183
00:12:25,536 --> 00:12:29,957
[pensive music continues]

184
00:12:31,667 --> 00:12:33,294
[rapid gunfire]

185
00:12:34,753 --> 00:12:35,796
[rapid gunfire]

186
00:12:37,381 --> 00:12:38,716
[rapid gunfire]

187
00:12:40,050 --> 00:12:41,469
[rapid gunfire]

188
00:12:42,511 --> 00:12:44,847
[rapid gunfire]

189
00:12:45,973 --> 00:12:51,020
[pensive music continues]

190
00:12:56,400 --> 00:12:58,194
[man] <i>Someone else opened fire.</i>

191
00:12:58,861 --> 00:13:01,447
<i>To start chaos</i>
<i>and turn it into a massacre.</i>

192
00:13:01,530 --> 00:13:06,994
[phone vibrating]

193
00:13:15,544 --> 00:13:17,546
LARA
YOU HAVE TO WATCH THIS

194
00:13:17,630 --> 00:13:22,092
[grim music playing]

195
00:13:39,527 --> 00:13:46,200
- [men yelling on video]
- [rapid gunfire]

196
00:13:46,700 --> 00:13:47,868
[reporter] <i>It's now confirmed</i>

197
00:13:47,952 --> 00:13:50,538
<i>that the video circulating</i>
<i>on social media came from the very place</i>

198
00:13:50,621 --> 00:13:54,875
<i>where Datu Rahman Abubakar was arrested</i>

199
00:13:54,959 --> 00:13:56,919
<i>for alleged gun smuggling.</i>

200
00:13:57,002 --> 00:13:58,254
<i>Yes, there's gun smuggling.</i>

201
00:13:58,337 --> 00:14:02,383
<i>But that's not enough justification</i>
<i>for killing innocent civilians.</i>

202
00:14:02,466 --> 00:14:04,426
<i>Whatever happened to due process?</i>

203
00:14:04,510 --> 00:14:06,053
<i>To protecting the innocent?</i>

204
00:14:06,136 --> 00:14:07,805
<i>Is that all gone now?</i>

205
00:14:07,888 --> 00:14:11,642
<i>Here he is, the team leader</i>
<i>of Task Force Alpha,</i>

206
00:14:11,725 --> 00:14:15,479
<i>allegedly responsible for the massacre</i>
<i>of an entire community.</i>

207
00:14:16,063 --> 00:14:19,775
<i>The Golden Boy</i>
<i>of the Special Investigation Division,</i>

208
00:14:20,276 --> 00:14:24,238
<i>Agent Marcus Reyes.</i>

209
00:14:24,321 --> 00:14:29,285
[tense music playing]

210
00:14:29,910 --> 00:14:31,495
- [glass shatters]
- [grunts]

211
00:14:31,579 --> 00:14:33,956
[breathing heavily]

212
00:14:34,748 --> 00:14:35,833
My God.

213
00:14:37,126 --> 00:14:39,169
My son couldn't have done this.

214
00:14:46,051 --> 00:14:49,388
[phone vibrating]

215
00:14:50,764 --> 00:14:53,183
[breathing heavily]

216
00:14:53,267 --> 00:14:55,352
[line ringing]

217
00:14:56,145 --> 00:14:59,607
- [phone vibrating]
- [breathing heavily]

218
00:15:00,149 --> 00:15:01,233
[phone thuds]

219
00:15:05,237 --> 00:15:06,989
Marcus, son.

220
00:15:12,202 --> 00:15:15,706
- [inhales]
- [object thuds]

221
00:15:18,417 --> 00:15:21,086
[woman] Free Datu Rahman!

222
00:15:21,670 --> 00:15:25,883
Free him! Justice for Zamboanga!

223
00:15:25,966 --> 00:15:27,843
- [car horn honking]
- [gate creaks open]

224
00:15:27,927 --> 00:15:29,386
PROTECT LIFE

225
00:15:29,470 --> 00:15:31,722
[indistinct chatter]

226
00:15:31,805 --> 00:15:33,807
You'll be imprisoned, too!

227
00:15:33,891 --> 00:15:35,935
- You'll be imprisoned!
- [people shouting]

228
00:15:36,018 --> 00:15:38,562
[indistinct shouting]

229
00:15:38,646 --> 00:15:40,064
[indistinct shouting]

230
00:15:42,900 --> 00:15:44,401
- [woman] You'll be imprisoned!
- [people shouting]

231
00:15:44,485 --> 00:15:47,988
[dramatic music playing]

232
00:15:50,824 --> 00:15:54,370
[indistinct shouting]

233
00:15:55,663 --> 00:15:59,833
You'll be imprisoned, too!
You're a murderer!

234
00:16:01,335 --> 00:16:06,340
- Justice! Justice for Zamboanga!
- [people shouting]

235
00:16:06,423 --> 00:16:08,968
- You'll be imprisoned!
- [people shouting]

236
00:16:09,051 --> 00:16:11,553
[overlapping chatter]

237
00:16:14,098 --> 00:16:18,394
[activists chanting] Justice!
Justice! Justice!

238
00:16:18,477 --> 00:16:20,729
Justice! Justice!

239
00:16:20,813 --> 00:16:22,022
Agent Reyes.

240
00:16:23,899 --> 00:16:24,942
How are you?

241
00:16:25,025 --> 00:16:29,321
[dramatic music continues]

242
00:16:41,500 --> 00:16:42,418
[footsteps]

243
00:16:42,501 --> 00:16:47,798
[ominous music playing]

244
00:16:47,881 --> 00:16:49,174
Marcus.

245
00:16:56,390 --> 00:16:58,600
I thought all files had been deleted?

246
00:16:58,684 --> 00:16:59,935
Where did that video come from?

247
00:17:00,853 --> 00:17:04,857
It seems one of the survivors
got Rustia's body cam.

248
00:17:04,940 --> 00:17:06,483
I'm sure that's who uploaded the footage.

249
00:17:09,945 --> 00:17:11,655
Lara, listen to me.

250
00:17:13,490 --> 00:17:15,325
The chaos happened on purpose.

251
00:17:16,577 --> 00:17:18,203
A different group fired at us.

252
00:17:18,287 --> 00:17:19,872
What do you mean?

253
00:17:19,955 --> 00:17:21,498
[ominous music continues]

254
00:17:21,582 --> 00:17:22,583
Reyes!

255
00:17:29,089 --> 00:17:30,090
Sir.

256
00:17:33,927 --> 00:17:36,346
What's the matter with you, Agent Reyes?

257
00:17:37,222 --> 00:17:40,267
The agency's reputation is being hit
because of your actions!

258
00:17:40,350 --> 00:17:42,352
- Goddamnit!
- Sir.

259
00:17:42,853 --> 00:17:45,522
That's what I wanted to explain,
but you didn't listen to me.

260
00:17:46,398 --> 00:17:48,275
Are you saying it's my fault now?

261
00:17:50,486 --> 00:17:51,737
No, sir.

262
00:17:51,820 --> 00:17:53,655
What I want to say is…

263
00:17:54,323 --> 00:17:56,200
There was an anomaly in our mission

264
00:17:56,283 --> 00:17:58,243
that caused a lot
of innocent people to die,

265
00:17:58,327 --> 00:18:00,454
that caused Harold to be left
behind and die.

266
00:18:01,330 --> 00:18:03,540
That's what I wanted
to explain to you, sir.

267
00:18:04,208 --> 00:18:05,167
Now…

268
00:18:05,959 --> 00:18:08,378
You have plenty
of opportunities to explain.

269
00:18:10,422 --> 00:18:11,673
Goddamnit.

270
00:18:14,468 --> 00:18:18,347
[ominous music continues]

271
00:18:33,612 --> 00:18:34,863
[music ends]

272
00:18:35,697 --> 00:18:36,782
[Jamilah exhales]

273
00:18:36,865 --> 00:18:41,328
[morose music playing]

274
00:18:45,124 --> 00:18:46,333
[Jamilah sniffles]

275
00:18:47,918 --> 00:18:49,878
[Jamilah crying]

276
00:18:52,548 --> 00:18:55,968
[Jamilah crying]

277
00:18:56,051 --> 00:18:57,511
Kah…

278
00:18:57,594 --> 00:19:03,308
[Jamilah crying]

279
00:19:03,392 --> 00:19:08,689
[morose music continues]

280
00:19:08,772 --> 00:19:12,067
[Jamilah crying]

281
00:19:18,115 --> 00:19:23,328
[music turns stirring]

282
00:19:43,223 --> 00:19:44,683
Someone suddenly spoke on the radio.

283
00:19:44,766 --> 00:19:46,018
[soldier] <i>Neutralize the area!</i>

284
00:19:46,101 --> 00:19:48,270
But I didn't hear anything like that.
Someone fired at us.

285
00:19:48,353 --> 00:19:50,772
[Azuelo] <i>So someone set up that chaos?</i>

286
00:19:50,856 --> 00:19:53,275
Yes. To massacre those in the island.

287
00:19:53,358 --> 00:19:56,737
[Jalil] <i>Why did they kill our people?</i>

288
00:19:56,820 --> 00:19:58,238
Why?!

289
00:19:58,322 --> 00:20:02,284
He is their leader.
Everyone thinks you're dead.

290
00:20:02,367 --> 00:20:07,539
[Jalil] I won't stop
until I get revenge for our people.

291
00:20:08,707 --> 00:20:10,459
[Lara] <i>If you really believe</i>
<i>you're being silenced,</i>

292
00:20:10,542 --> 00:20:13,295
<i>then uncover the truth</i>
<i>before it's too late.</i>

293
00:20:15,005 --> 00:20:16,131
- Ugh…
- Argh!

294
00:20:16,215 --> 00:20:17,674
[gunshot blasts]

295
00:20:19,593 --> 00:20:22,346
- Argh!
- Argh!

296
00:20:22,429 --> 00:20:23,513
[officer] You're Muslim, right?

297
00:20:23,597 --> 00:20:26,808
You might let Datu Rahman escape.

298
00:20:26,892 --> 00:20:28,852
You have to save Datu Rahman.

299
00:20:30,062 --> 00:20:34,775
[Jalil] <i>I will correct all this.</i>
<i>I know Amah is innocent.</i>

300
00:20:34,858 --> 00:20:38,570
Standing in front of me now
to kill my people!

301
00:20:38,654 --> 00:20:40,239
I didn't want that!

302
00:20:40,322 --> 00:20:41,907
I never wanted what happened!

303
00:20:41,990 --> 00:20:47,037
[woman protestor]
Justice for Zamboanga! Free Datu Rahman!

304
00:20:47,120 --> 00:20:48,121
[crowd] Justice! Justice!

305
00:20:48,205 --> 00:20:49,248
- Justice!
- We're being mobbed!

306
00:20:49,331 --> 00:20:51,416
- We need crowd control assistance.
- Justice!

307
00:20:51,500 --> 00:20:53,210
[indistinct shouting]

308
00:20:53,293 --> 00:20:54,628
[Lara] All units, Command.

309
00:20:54,711 --> 00:20:57,381
Priority one, crowd control
on vehicle two.

310
00:20:57,464 --> 00:21:00,550
Secure the detainee, and move him
to lead vehicle now!

311
00:21:01,134 --> 00:21:04,012
- Argh! Argh! Argh!
- Argh! Argh!

312
00:21:04,096 --> 00:21:06,223
- Ugh…
- Argh!

313
00:21:06,306 --> 00:21:08,892
- Argh! Argh!
- Ugh…
